lead_paragraph: United States Representatives Edward R. Roybal and Mervyn M. Dymally, Democrats who between them have served in Congress for four decades, announced on Monday that they would not seek re-election. Mr. Roybal, the 75-year-old dean of Los Angeles's Hispanic elected officials, cited the poor health of his wife.

headline.main: 2 California Representatives Say They Will Not Run Again
